(10, 1, '2019-01-28 08:29:08', '2019-01-28 08:29:08', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I believe that the human mind evolved as the&nbsp;separate brain neural-functions started to&nbsp;connect up . To begin with the&nbsp;neural-functions&nbsp;for, say, eating were completely separate from those for looking out for predator danger. The mind as we think of it now came about as these separated parts of the brain’s activity became more and more connected. Being able to have a sandwich whilst also watch out for predators was selected for.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Continue that thought experiment forward to contemporary humans. Whatever selection pressure there happened to&nbsp; be produced more and more connected brains where the ability to think of and execute plans, be flexible, adaptable etc has flourished.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>But the process is still in progress. Our minds haven’t yet fully developed and we humans still struggle to fit the modern world into our biologically disconnected brain structure.&nbsp;This can lead to odd dichotomies like a person being able to hold two contradictory views at the same time from two different standpoints and for that not to be ridiculous. We could call it empathy. Call it what you like, it’s fundamentally a separation of mind thing.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>My feeling is the more connected the better. Being stoned connects parts of my mind in a more fluid way than how it works when I’m straight. I am more easily able to hold several concepts in my mind at any one time and flick between them at will without having to re-remember. Quite handy when you\'re doing computer programming for instance.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Perhaps that’s not how it works. Perhaps the pot simply removes self imposed inhibitions in my mind which would be removed if I were a more enlightened buddhist kinda dude. But I don’t think so.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I think there is a reason for the odd fact that we have cannabinoid receptors in our bodies at all. I think that perhaps that careful research might support a hypothesis that pot in the recent 10,000 years of human history was as important to our development as alcohol.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Some people say alcohol&nbsp; is responsible for the agricultural revolution. Shit idea THAT was. People wanted beer, needed crops, stopped being hunter gathers, got fat and unhappy.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Others say that even coming down from the trees was a bad idea and we should have stayed put in the prime-evil soup like god intended.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Mind you, some people will say anything.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Point is... When I’m stoned I feel like I could undertake that research. Of course I never would, but I could certainly see myself writing the Wei Zang Chronicles and many other useful things.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When I’m not stoned… well heck…. Life is just a bit average you know?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Manifesto', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'home', '', '', '2019-01-30 07:53:53', '2019-01-30 07:53:53', '', 0, 'https://diary-of-a-pothead.com/?page_id=10', 0, 'page', '', 0),
